title.rendered: Project ZED Unveils Art Basel 2023 Edition

content.rendered:
Project ZED Unveils Art Basel Edition: A Fusion of Fashion, Art, and Sustainability

Miami, FL December 1st, 2023 As the excitement builds for Miami Art Week, the highly anticipated 3rd annual Project ZED, presented by Miami Swim Week, is set to redefine the intersection of fashion, art, and sustainability. The event promises an immersive experience, showcasing renowned designers and artists, while emphasizing a commitment to eco-conscious practices.

Event Highlights:

Fashion Extravaganza: Immerse yourself in a spectacular blend of fashion shows, art installations, and exhibitions during Art Basel Week in Miami's Design District. Witness the creativity of acclaimed designers and the brilliance of renowned artists, all converging to celebrate the spirit of artistic innovation.

Artistic Activations:

HydroThreads Art Installation: Explore the chic fusion of Smart Swimsuits and Smart Water in a transparent cube. Cascading threads in brand-inspired hues create a dynamic dance, symbolizing the intersection of style, sustainability, and purity.

Ema Savahl's Glow-in-the-Dark Showcase: Experience the enchanting allure of luminous suits in a captivating showcase. Models adorned in glow-in-the-dark art create a spellbinding presentation that seamlessly blends with a mesmerizing performance.

Local Art Exhibition: Immerse yourself in the works of talented local artists Franco Bracho, Merz Marina, Neto Sansone, and Katey Jay Art & Design.

Featured Runway Shows

7:4pm-

Megan Mae Miami Swimwear

ELSA DRESS COUTURE

Milus Rose

Andrea Venturoli

Love For Upcycling

9:15pm-

Amarotto Swimwear

My Mokondo

Pio Beachwear

Neidy Parra

Smart Swimsuits

Ema Savahl Closing Show

Co-hosts

Project Zed is cohosted by MM Collective and Katia Productions -A state-of-the-art full-service

film studio, situated in the heart of Miamis Design District that provides top-notch facilities for

all your production needs.

Sponsors:

MM Collective, Katia Productions, New York Makeup Academy, UNITE Hair, Smartwater, Inlist,

Ron Barcel Rum, Voga Italia, Lagoon Bay, Hello Gorgeous, Heliz Vodka, are proud sponsors,

aligning the event with a commitment to visual excellence and social consciousness.

Event details

Tickets are available HERE and join us on December 07th at 6:30 pm at SOUND STAGE -

Design District (4151 NW 2nd Ave, Miami, FL, 33127) for an unforgettable evening of glamour,

innovation, and sustainability. Project ZED - Art Basel Edition is powered by Miami Swim

Week- The Shows
